[[Image:Kitakatsuragi District in Nara prefecture Ja.png|thumb|250px|Location of Kitakatsuragi District in Nara Prefecture]] {{nihongo|'''Kitakatsuragi'''|北葛城郡|Kitakatsuragi-gun}} is a [[:en:Districts of Japan|district]] located in [[:en:Nara Prefecture|Nara Prefecture]], [[:en:Japan|Japan]].
As of 2003, the district has an estimated [[population]] of 134,816 and a [[:en:Population density|density]] of 1,886.07 persons per km<sup>2</sup>. The total area is 71.48&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>.
==Towns and villages== *[[:en:Kanmaki, Nara|Kanmaki]] *[[:en:Kawai, Nara|Kawai]] *[[:en:Kōryō, Nara|Kōryō]] *[[:en:Ōji, Nara|Ōji]]
==Mergers== *On October 1, 2004 the towns of [[Shinjō, Nara|Shinjō]] and [[Taima, Nara|Taima]] merged to form the new city of [[:en:Katsuragi, Nara|Katsuragi]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=総務省｜令和2nd year 版 地方財政白書｜資料編 〔附属資料〕 昭和60th year 度以降の市町村合併の実績 |trans-title=Record of Municipal Mergers Since Showa 60 |url=https://www.soumu.go.jp/menu_seisaku/hakusyo/chihou/32data/2020data/r02czs05-03.html |access-date=2024-02-28 |website=総務省 |language=ja}}</ref>
